The numbers which can be expressed as a square of a prime will have exactly 3 divisors. Like for32, it has 3 divisors 1, 3,32.

title.description: How many integers in the set 1,2,3,......,100 have exactly 3 divisors?

ansDescription.text:
Explanation:  

Total balls are 100  

Balls that are equally divided among students = 100-7=93

Let the number of students be a .

As, the value of ‘a’ can lie between 10 to 60.  

So,possible value of a is 31. ie. factor of 93.  

When 125 balls are equally distributed among 31 students then only 1 ball remain undistributed.
